  "body": "So I started using namespaces for the first time, and I ran:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nkubectl get pods\r\n```\r\n\r\nnothing was showing up...I was really confused, debugging stuff for 30+ minutes..\r\nfinally I was like, even tho this is really dumb, maybe they are behind a namespace, so I did:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nkubectl get pods --namespace=mine\r\n```\r\n\r\nand finally my pods showed up.  so yes there is:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nkubectl get pods --all-namespaces\r\n```\r\n\r\nbut this should really be the default, shouldn't it?  You will save people a lot of time if you make this fix. tbh, this is a really crappy cli design in this case.\r\n",
